OR OTHERWISE.

IF THE APPLICATION HAVE ANY BUGS PLEASE REPORT ME,I WILL
GENERATE AN UPDATE TO ELIMINATE THE ERRORS.

P.S.

SORRY FOR MY BAD ENGLISH..


@endnode

@node required "What you need to run Magic-Exchange"

You need following things to start Magic-Exchange.

- Amiga 500/500+/600/1000/1200/2000/2500/3000(T)/4000(T)

- 25KB Free Memory

- Kickstart 2.x or higher

- Installed Magic-User-Interface (MUI) Version 3.x

- 51200 Bytes of Stack

- Installed ARexx system

That's it.

@endnode


@node features "Features List from Magic-Exchange"

- Absolutly font and sizeadaptive Gui

- Completely localized

- Hotkey Usage

- Info about Task (e.g. Taskname,Taskprio)

- Task-Prio changer (Give task's new priority)

- Jump to all Publicscreens if Open

- Bubblehelp for Information on Buttons Actions ect.

- All Commoditie command functions

- Hotkey Support

- Configurable via TOOLTYPES

- ARexx Interface

@endnode

@node install "Installation of Magic-Exchange"

Copy Exchange, Exchange.info, Exchange.guide and Exchange.guide.info to
a Drawer you Like. e.g Work:E-Tools/Cx/

Pick your favorit language from the catalogs dir and put it into the Locale:catalogs drawer.

that's it.

@endnode

@node usage "How to use Magic-Exchange"

First the configuring of Magic-Exchange.

The Exchange.info contains many Tooltypes called

DONOTWAIT   (Kick the Nervously requester if Exchange in Wbstartup)
CX_PRIORITY (Specified Priority of Magic-Exchange Default = 0)
CX_POPUP    (If set it to FALSE the Gui will not PopUp Default=TRUE)
CX_HOTKEY   (defines any Hotkey yout want DEFAULT = ctrl alt help)
CX_NOREQ    (If it set to YES no requester will inform you when commodtie
             Removed ect. For Arexx-Interface) DEFAULT=NO

CX_LISTFILE (You have to specified an Path with name for the arexx command
             me_getcxlst) DEFAULT=t:cxlst


Next The Usage....


First the Gadgets

- The Listview displays all started commodities in system.

 - The Big Gadget right from Listview Displays the Informationtext
   from Selected commodity in Listview. (ONE KLICK IN LISTVIEW-ENTRY!!)

- The Actiongroup.
  
 - Hide  Hide the commoditie Interface

 - Show  Show the commoditie Interface

 - The Cycle makes selected commoditie Aktiv or InActiv
   (ONE KLICK IN LISTVIEW-ENTRY!!)

 - Remove will Remove the selected commodity from System

 - Last Gadget on left displays the Taskinformation
   when Doubleklick in Listview-Entry

 - Last Gadget on right Update the Taskprio from comodity
   when Doubleklick in Listview-Entry



Next the Menus.....

- Projekt

  About - displays Programinformation

  Quit  - end the Application

- Commodities

  Here we have 2 Functions to all Commoditie functions.
  that will Action to All or Selected commodities.

  Remove  will remove commodities

  Show    will Popup commodities Gui (if it have)

  Hide    will Hide  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ or Open

  Activate will activate commodities

  Deactivate will deactivate active commodities.


That's it

@endnode

@node arex "The Magic-Exchange arexx interface"

An user of Amiga Group in the University in Munich wrote to me.
"Please add an Arexx port to magic-exchange. I use arexx very very often"...

Okay here they comes.

The Arexx Command's

NAME             TEMPLATE       DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CX_Select        NAME/A         Select an commoditie in list if it exists.
CX_GetList       ------         Save an commoditie list to any Path SEE ALSO @{"Usage" LINK usage} TOOLTYPES
CX_Remove        ------         Remove an commoditie Do CX_Select bevor use this command
CX_Deactivate    ------         Activate an commoditie Do CX_Select bevor use this command
CX_Activate      ------         Deactivate an commoditie Do CX_Select bevor use this command
CX_Priority      PRIO/A         Sets the Priority of an commoditie Do CX_Select bevor use this command
CX_RemoveAll     ------         Remove all commodities

@endnode

